<informationtext name="Information">
<![CDATA[
<p><span>The Department of Design offers a creative, challenging, and flexible approach to the study of design with emphasis on socially responsible, human-centered, and sustainable practice.</span></p>
<h2>The Program</h2>
<p>The Department of Design takes a comprehensive, liberal arts approach to design education. We help students make connections across different design disciplines while learning through both theory and practice. This integration is essential: today's most pressing challenges—from climate resilience to social equity to technological change—demand designers who can bring creativity, curiosity, and rigor to complex, dynamic problems. As part of a research-oriented (R1) university, we encourage students to extend their skills and knowledge by taking courses from other disciplines that complement our curriculum.</p>
<p>Our curriculum emphasizes socially responsible, human-centered, ethically grounded, and sustainable practice. Students build foundational skills in drawing, color, form, and digital tools, then pursue specialized interests through studio work, history and theory courses, and research-based projects. Many students enhance their education through internships with design firms and museums, study abroad programs, student clubs and chapters of professional organizations, and independent research.</p>
<p>Design graduates from UC Davis work in various areas, including exhibition design, fashion, information design, interactive design, UI/UX, product design, textiles, visual communications, and sustainable design. Others pursue graduate study or launch their own design practices.</p>
<p>For more details, contact <a href="https://arts.ucdavis.edu/design-advisors" title="Advising Resources in Design"><span class="title">Advising Resources in Design</span></a> in 101 Art Building; 530-752-0890.</p>
]]>
</informationtext>
